2.REVERT MERGE
              git revert HEAD   //we want revert last commit (HEAD commit)

Note: it get some error:
                        no -m was given!
      when the commit has to parent
      we need to declare to git choose witch one?
      it is not used parent based on current branch like moving HEAD!

we use:
       "git revert -m 1 HEAD"
       it means revert HEAD to first parent
       who is he?
       the first one is the main one(ec1a607)               //merge commit has two pointer!
                                                            //by 1, we say him go back to the commit
                                                            //that exist on current branch

